import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['speed'], bins='auto', edgecolor='black')
    plt.xlabel('Wind Speed (m/s)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of wind speed across all wind vectors?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    scatter = plt.scatter(data['latitude'], data['longitude'], c=data['dir'], cmap='viridis')
    plt.colorbar(scatter, label='Wind Direction (degrees)')
    plt.xlabel('Latitude')
    plt.ylabel('Longitude')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title('How does wind direction vary across different latitude and longitude coordinates?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    box_plot_data = data.groupby('dirCat')['speed'].apply(list)
    plt.boxplot(box_plot_data, labels=box_plot_data.index)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.xlabel('Wind Direction Categories')
    plt.ylabel('Wind Speed (m/s)')
    plt.title('How does wind speed vary across different wind direction categories?', wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
